<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,648,1569,1699]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
DISTRIBUTION. — This species is more abundant in the forested area of the country (ER IV), although it is common in ER II, III and V and also present in ER I. 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[113,280,1649,1673]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" pagination="207 - 236" refId="ref29004" refString="STERNFELD L. 1908 b. - Die Schlangenfauna Togos. Mittheilungen Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 4: 207 - 236." type="journal article" year="1908">Sternfeld (1908b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[291,380,1649,1673]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" refId="ref29026" refString="STERNFELD L. 1909. - Die Schlangen Togos, in Die Fauna der deutschen Kolonien 1 (1): iv + 29 p., map." type="book" year="1909">1909: 23</bibRefCitation>
) recorded this species from Missahohe and Bismarkburg (now Adele) and from the
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[675,1212,215,371]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
Kete-Kratchi, now in 
<collectingCountry box="[901,972,215,239]" name="Ghana" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Ghana</collectingCountry>
. It was also mentioned from 
<collectingCountry box="[729,778,241,265]" name="Togo" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Togo</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="BROADLEY D. G." box="[811,969,241,265]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref26344" refString="BROADLEY D. G. 1968. - A review of the African cobras of the genus Naja (Serpentes: Elapidae). Arnoldia Rhodesia 3 (29): 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1968">Broadley (1968)</bibRefCitation>
