<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[675,1210,406,591]" box="[677,767,406,433]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[675,1210,406,591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
This species presents two morphs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1121,438,465]" name="Togo" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Togo</collectingCountry>
, namely a “savannah morph” observed in Aledjo (T 192) area and a “forest morph” in ER IV. They differ by the dorsal yellow rings, which are more contrasting in specimens of the savannah morph.
</paragraph>
